  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (205°C). Season the veal cutlets with salt and pepper.",
    "Heat vegetable oil in a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add cutlets and cook until golden brown on both sides, about 2-3 minutes per side.",
    "Transfer cutlets to a plate. Deglaze the pan with soy sauce, mirin, vinegar, sesame oil, and pepper flakes, scraping any bits from the bottom of the pan. Bring to simmer.",
    "Return veal cutlets to the pan and add sliced scallions and fresh cilantro. Cook for an additional 2-3 minutes or until heated through.",
    "Serve hot with steamed vegetables on the side."
